history.content: Campus systems send out a confusing error message if a student can't enroll in a class for any reason (like your enrollment category is full for 16A) that appears to claim it is because of time conflicts.  This is just not true for departments that enable time conflicts which we do for both CS and EE (and EECS) classes.

Hi, 

I'm currently enrolled in CS61b and I tried to add EE16a, but it didn't let me because the lab time conflicts with the 61b lecture. Is there a way to override it so I can enroll in 16a? I figured that since 61b has a webcast this could be feasible. 

Thanks!
